history.content:
I took the course last semester, and it's a relatively straightforward course. Programming assignments take a fair bit of time, but I learned more in that class than most other courses I took.

Most of the material doesn't assume much more than knowing simple linear algebra (you have to implement Matmul for one of the HWs), and C programming.

children.subject: All graduate courses require instructor permission for undergrads to enroll. The details of how the instructor decides which undergrads to accept is up to the instructor, but you would need to get a permission code regardless of the policy.
